cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with face detection, landmark localization, pose estimation, and gender recognition, which are all related to computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses deep convolutional neural networks (CNN) and multi-task learning algorithms, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with multimedia and image processing, which are related to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), respectively.
